    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-02-28T12:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1960-02-28T12:15:00-05:00" n="213"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                <head>213. Memorandum of a Conversation, San Carlos de Bariloche, February 28, 1960,
                    2:15 p.m.<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d213fn1">Source: Department of State,
                        Conference Files: Lot 64 D 559, CF 1596. Confidential. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RRRJ1">Rubottom</persName>. See also <ref target="#d209"
                            >Documents 209</ref>–<ref target="#d212">212</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">US/<gloss target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>/10</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>San Carlos de Bariloche</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1960-02-28T14:15:00-03:00"
                            >February 28, 1960, 2:15 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">US</hi>
                        <list>
                            <item>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">Herter</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Assistant Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RRRJ1"
                                    >Rubottom</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Argentina</hi>
                        <list>
                            <item>President <persName corresp="#p_FA1">Frondizi</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Foreign Minister Taboada</item>
                            <item>Ambassador Del Carril</item>
                            <item>Minister Orfila</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Argentine Participation in Economic Meetings</item>
                </list>
                <p>As the meeting broke up, the Foreign Minister returned to a subject which he had
                    previously raised twice in the presence of the Secretary, namely, Argentina’s
                    desire to have its interests considered in any future economic discussions
                    involving the European countries, Canada and the U.S. They would like to be an
                    observer at such <pb facs="0659" n="619" xml:id="pg_619"/> meetings, if
                    possible. He promised to furnish Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RRRJ1"
                        >Rubottom</persName> with a memorandum on this subject.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d213fn2">Not found in Department of State files.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
